African resident (orange dots, solid regression line; 
						n = 10) and European migrant (blue triangles, dashed regression line; 
						n = 26) stonechats initiated Zugunruhe at progressively younger ages when hatched late in the season under European day length conditions. Inlay: pairs of African (right) and European (left) stonechats; females are less conspicuously colored than males. Drawing is by H. Kacher.
